-- Air Companies Complain on Airbus, Boeing Subsidies, Tribune Says
-- B y   D a v i d   W h i t e h o u s e
-- 2010-10-07T05:22:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-07/air-companies-complain-on-airbus-boeing-export-subsidies-tribune-says.html
Nine air companies in France, the
U.K., Germany and Spain, as well as the U.S. Air Transport
Association, will write to their finance ministries and the OECD
to protest the system of export credits used for the purchase of
Boeing Co. and Airbus SAS planes, La Tribune reported.  The letter will be sent on Oct. 8, the newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Whitehouse at 
 dwhitehouse1@bloomberg.net  